   <p><placeName ref="cwgk:P00002311">Dixon</placeName> / <placeName ref="cwgk:P00002312">Webster Co</placeName> <placeName ref="cwgk:P001800">Ky </placeName><date when="1865-09-24">Sept 24<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> 1865</date>
<lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N001000">Mr Bramlett</persName><lb/>Sir</p>
<p>yours truly
<lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N00008707">Thos. J. Trice</persName></p>
<p>we have no soldiers here now to protect us and we are Bound to do something or go by the Board<pb/></p>
<p>Dixon Webster Co. Ky.
<lb/><date when="1865-09-24">Sep. 24, '65</date><figure type="hr"/></p>
<p>Trice, Thomas J.
<lb/>To Govener<figure type="hr"/></p>
<p>States that that portion of the country is overrun by thieves and robbers, who are stealing horses, and robbing and plundering houses. Asks permission to raise a squad of men, who will arm and mount himself, for the purpose of bringing them to justice<figure type="hr"/></p>
<p>Ans. <date when="1865-10-03">Oct 3<hi rend="sup">d</hi>, 65</date>. Lt Bk B, p 294.<figure type="hr"/>
<lb/>Rec. <orgName ref="cwgk:O00000920">I. G. O.</orgName> <date when="1865-10-03">Oct 3<hi rend="sup">d</hi> 1865</date></p>
  </body>
